<b>Posted On:</b> 9:13 p.m. 14/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Calling out to all GMs<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=904" TARGET=_self>Calling out to all GMs</A> (Galford Teveril[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>They are working on making the server stable for everyone and getting all the initial bugs out. Lets not expect miracles. We've gotten a ton of good ideas and they're being filtered now to find out which ones are feesable and which ones need to be put on the "Near Future" list.

<P>Geiger
<P>&gt; I'm just curious as to if anything at all is being done about
<BR>&gt; PvP in EQ. There have been many complaints and many suggestions
<BR>&gt; here on this board as well as in game, yet I don't see anything
<BR>&gt; happening at all. I quit playing on the PvP server because it is
<BR>&gt; apparant that you guys are doing NOTHING! Now I know you are
<BR>&gt; having server stability problems and everything, but that does
<BR>&gt; not mean that EVERY gm has to work on them. I thought that each
<BR>&gt; server had it's own designated gm, maybe I'm wrong. My point is
<BR>&gt; this, PvP needs a lot of work, and there have been many
<BR>&gt; wonderful suggestions here on this board. This board was put up
<BR>&gt; in order for us to give you guys feedback as to what we thought
<BR>&gt; of PvP, yet it seems as if you are not fullfilling your part of
<BR>&gt; the bargain. If I'm wrong, I'm sorry, but when I see many posts
<BR>&gt; over the same thing, I get the feeling that nothing is being
<BR>&gt; done.
<BR>&gt; Thanks for your time,
<BR>&gt; Galford Teveril of Covetous Crew
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
